      <div xml:id="NA7-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">EN, ER: itu paṭṭapiṉṟai varaiyātu kiḻavōṉ neṭṭiṭai kaḻintu poruḷvayiṉ piriya āṟṟāḷāya talaivikkut (ET: talaimakaṭkut) tōḻi colliyatu. EV: kaḷavoḻukkam veḷippaṭṭa piṉpum talaimakaṉ varaiyātu poruḷvayiṉ pirintu neṭun tūram ceṉṟāṉ. ataṉāl āṟṟāḷākiya talaiviyai tōḻi avar kuṟitta kār kālam vantuṟṟatu; ippoḻutē vantu niṉṉai varaintu koḷvar; varuntātoḻiyeṉa āṟṟuvittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said to HER who was unable to bear it when HE separated for the sake of wealth after a long interval had passed of not marrying after it had happened. EV: After the secret conduct had become public without marrying HE separated for the sake of wealth [and] went to a far distance. How the confidante apprised HER, who was unable to bear it because of that, of the coming of the rainy season which he had indicated; how she comforted “as this season has come he will take you in marriage; stop suffering.”</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA7">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            cūruṭai naṉantalaic cuṉainīr malkap</l>
<l>            peruvarai yaṭukkat taruvi yārppak</l>
<l>            kallalait tiḻitaruṅ kaṭuvaraṟ kāṉyāṟṟuk</l>
<l>            kaḻaimāy nīttaṅ kāṭalai yārppat</l>
<l>            taḻaṅkukura lēṟoṭu muḻaṅki vāṉa </l>
<l>            miṉṉē peyya miṉṉumāṟ ṟōḻi</l>
<l>            veṇṇe laruntiya varinutal yāṉai</l>
<l>            taṇṇaṟuñ cilampiṟ ṟuñcuñ</l>
<l>            ciṟiyilaic cantiṉa vāṭuperuṅ kāṭṭē.</l>

        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>The sky, rumbling with loud-voiced thunder,</l>
        <l rend="indent2">so that the water in the mountain pools increases in the fearful vast area,</l>
	    <l rend="indent2">so that waterfalls roar on the side of the big mountain,</l>
	    <l rend="indent2">so that the bamboo-hiding<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kaḻai māy</term>: either so deep as to cover the bamboo growing on the shore, or, thus T.V.G., deeper than the length of the bamboo rod used for steering a boat/raft.</note> flood roars, shaking the wilderness,</l>
        <l rend="indent">in the fast coming forest river, which tumbles down</l>
        <l rend="indent3">hitting stones,</l>
        <l>– just now it flashes indeed, friend, so that it rains</l>
        <l rend="indent">on the withering great wilderness of small-leaved sandal trees,</l>
        <l rend="indent2">where the elephant with lined forehead, that has eaten white</l>
        <l rend="indent2">paddy<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">veṇṇel</term> is explained here by T.V.G. as the kind of grain produced by bamboo (presumably because it is unclear how white paddy should have come to the wilderness).</note>, sleeps on the cool fragrant mountain side.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
